The paper deals with the problem of finding whether there exist at most k vertices in a graph whose deletion results in a graph of pathwidth at most one. This problem is related to graph theory and computational complexity, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a graph parameter and algorithmic techniques. "cs.CC" (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the NP-completeness of the problem. "cs.CG" (Computational Geometry) is another possibility as the paper deals with graph structures. "cs.GT" (Computer Science and Game Theory) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graph structures and optimization.
